{#-
  California SB 1235 / 10 CCR § 914 — Sales-Based Financing Disclosure.

  Source-of-truth dossier: docs/compliance/01_california.md, section
  "What 10 CCR § 914 requires for MCA disclosures."

  This template MUST match the regulator's prescribed form line-by-line.
  Variables ({{ }}) are runtime substitutions only — every literal
  regulatory string is from the dossier verbatim. No {% if %} branches
  alter the regulation's text; conditional rows (Estimated Monthly Cost
  insert; "no interest" suffix on Row 2; "finance charge will not
  increase" on Row 3) are emitted only when the regulation says they
  apply.

  Required context variables:
    financer_name              str   — funder/lender name
    funding_provided           str   — formatted dollars, gross advance
    recipient_funds            str   — net delivered to merchant
    recipient_funds_lt_funding bool  — true when payments to others are deducted
    pays_third_party_payoffs   bool  — true when financing pays off other obligations
    third_party_payoff_note    str   — short explanation when above is true
    apr                        str   — formatted percent, e.g. "36.50%"
    payment_channel            str   — e.g. "credit card receipts"
    avg_monthly_income         str   — formatted dollars per § 930/§ 931
    finance_is_fee_based       bool  — true for typical MCA (no interest accrual)
    finance_charge             str   — formatted dollars per § 943
    finance_charge_can_increase bool — false for typical MCA
    estimated_total_payment    str   — formatted dollars
    estimated_payment_amount   str   — formatted dollars (e.g. "487.00")
    estimated_payment_freq     str   — e.g. "business day", "week"
    irregular_payments_note    str   — empty string if none
    payment_terms_text         str   — pre-rendered (split-rate / preset+true-up / minimum)
    estimated_term             str   — formatted per § 901 (days if <=1y, else "Y years M months")
    estimated_term_explanation str   — short text on income assumption
    has_monthly_cost_insert    bool  — true when periodic payment is non-monthly (i.e. all MCAs)
    estimated_monthly_cost     str   — formatted dollars (or list) per § 942
    monthly_cost_derivation    str   — short explanation
    prepayment_finance_charge_text str — Row 8 content
    prepayment_additional_fee_text str — Row 9 content
    rendered_at                str   — ISO date for the rendering
-#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Commercial Financing Disclosure — California (SB 1235)</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: -apple-system, sans-serif; max-width: 760px; margin: 24px auto;
         color: #111; }
  h1   { font-size: 18px; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 12px 0; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid #555; padding: 8px 10px; vertical-align: top;
           font-size: 12px; }
  th    { background: #f0f0f0; text-align: left; }
  .col1 { width: 22%; font-weight: 600; }
  .col2 { width: 22%; }
  .col3 { width: 56%; }
  .footer { margin-top: 16px; font-size: 11px; color: #333; }
  .meta   { font-size: 10px; color: #666; margin-top: 6px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Commercial Financing Disclosure</h1>
<p class="meta">California — 10 CCR § 914. Provider: {{ financer_name }}.</p>

<table>
<thead>
<tr><th class="col1">&nbsp;</th><th class="col2">&nbsp;</th><th class="col3">&nbsp;</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>

{#- Row 1 — Funding Provided -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Funding Provided</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ funding_provided }}</td>
  <td class="col3">
    This is how much funding {{ financer_name }} will provide.
    {%- if recipient_funds_lt_funding %}
    Due to deductions or payments to others, the total funds that will be
    provided to you directly is {{ recipient_funds }}. For more information
    on what amounts will be deducted, please review the attached document
    "Itemization of Amount Financed."
    {%- endif %}
    {%- if pays_third_party_payoffs %}
    {{ third_party_payoff_note }}
    {%- endif %}
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Row 2 — Estimated APR -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Annual Percentage Rate (APR)</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ apr }}</td>
  <td class="col3">
    APR is the estimated cost of your financing expressed as a yearly rate.
    APR incorporates the amount and timing of the funding you receive,
    fees you pay, and the periodic payments you make. This calculation
    assumes your estimated average monthly income through {{ payment_channel }}
    will be {{ avg_monthly_income }}. Since your actual income may vary
    from our estimate, your effective APR may also vary.
    {%- if finance_is_fee_based %}
    APR is not an interest rate. The cost of this financing is based upon
    fees charged by {{ financer_name }} rather than interest that accrues
    over time.
    {%- endif %}
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Row 3 — Finance Charge -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Finance Charge</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ finance_charge }}</td>
  <td class="col3">
    This is the dollar cost of your financing.
    {%- if not finance_charge_can_increase %}
    Your finance charge will not increase if you take longer to pay off
    what you owe.
    {%- endif %}
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Row 4 — Estimated Total Payment Amount -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Total Payment Amount</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ estimated_total_payment }}</td>
  <td class="col3">
    This is the total dollar amount of payments we estimate you will make
    under the contract.
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Optional inserted row — Estimated Monthly Cost (for non-monthly periodic
    payments, i.e. all MCAs). Per § 914 this row is inserted BELOW Row 4. -#}
{%- if has_monthly_cost_insert %}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Monthly Cost</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ estimated_monthly_cost }}</td>
  <td class="col3">{{ monthly_cost_derivation }}</td>
</tr>
{%- endif %}

{#- Row 5 — Estimated Payment.
    Per § 914 cols 2+3 are combined: average periodic payment per § 942
    followed by "/" and frequency, plus dates+amounts of irregular payments. -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Payment</td>
  <td class="col2" colspan="2">
    {{ estimated_payment_amount }} / {{ estimated_payment_freq }}
    {%- if irregular_payments_note %}
    <br>{{ irregular_payments_note }}
    {%- endif %}
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Row 6 — Payment Terms.
    Per § 914 cols 2+3 are combined; content depends on the payment
    structure (split rate / preset+true-up / minimum). The caller
    pre-renders the appropriate variant per dossier guidance. -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Payment Terms</td>
  <td class="col2" colspan="2">{{ payment_terms_text }}</td>
</tr>

{#- Row 7 — Estimated Term -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Term</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ estimated_term }}</td>
  <td class="col3">{{ estimated_term_explanation }}</td>
</tr>

{#- Rows 8 & 9 — Prepayment.
    Per § 914 col 1 of rows 8 and 9 is combined as "Prepayment".
    Each row's cols 2+3 are also combined. -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1" rowspan="2">Prepayment</td>
  <td class="col2" colspan="2">{{ prepayment_finance_charge_text }}</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td class="col2" colspan="2">{{ prepayment_additional_fee_text }}</td>
</tr>

</tbody>
</table>

<p class="footer">California Applicable law requires this information to be provided to you to help you make an informed decision.</p>

<p class="meta">Generated by AEGIS on {{ rendered_at }}. Per 10 CCR § 901.</p>
</body>
</html>
